s\", \"from\": 1444, \"to\": 1461}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris is the epicentre of the Games, which open on July 26.\", \"from\": 1531, \"to\": 1590, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1531, \"end\": 1536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2594559845082104e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the epicentre\", \"from\": 1540, \"to\": 1553}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1557, \"to\": 1566}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 1582, \"to\": 1586}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The idea of the flame\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s long relay was to bring all of France and the Francophone world together in a joyous celebration of the first Olympic Games held in Paris for a century.\", \"from\": 1592, \"to\": 1770, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1649, \"end\": 1655, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999920754212547, \"rank\": 4.918204155904007e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1664, \"end\": 1675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999996891684105, \"rank\": 3.107014095726342e-07, \"text\": \"Francophone\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1750, \"end\": 1755, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2594559845082104e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The idea\", \"from\": 1592, \"to\": 1600}, {\"ngram\": \"the flame\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s long relay\", \"from\": 1604, \"to\": 1628}, {\"ngram\": \"a joyous celebration\", \"from\": 1694, \"to\": 1714}, {\"ngram\": \"the first Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1718, \"to\": 1741}, {\"ngram\": \"a century\", \"from\": 1760, \"to\": 1769}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, France has endured a season of bitter division since the flame\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Marseille welcome, and the country finds itself at a chaotic political impasse.\", \"from\": 1771, \"to\": 1926, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1780, \"end\": 1786, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999920754212547, \"rank\": 4.918204155904007e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1847, \"end\": 1856, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.699817267597317e-15, \"text\": \"Marseille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a season\", \"from\": 1799, \"to\": 1807}, {\"ngram\": \"bitter division\", \"from\": 1811, \"to\": 1826}, {\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 1870, \"to\": 1881}, {\"ngram\": \"a chaotic political impasse\", \"from\": 1898, \"to\": 1925}]}, {\"sentence\": \"President Emmanuel Macron chose to dissolve the National Assembly in June and call legislative elections.\", \"from\": 1928, \"to\": 2033, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1938, \"end\": 1953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 1976, \"end\": 1993, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Assembly\", \"score\": 0.9999986073749516, \"rank\": 1.0751718820231193e-06, \"text\": \"National Assembly\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Assembly\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Assembly\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"June\", \"from\": 1997, \"to\": 2001}, {\"ngram\": \"legislative elections\", \"from\": 2011, \"to\": 2032}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One week after the vote produced a parliament divided among left-wing, centrist and right-wing blocs, none with an absolute majority, no agreement on a governing coalition has been reached.\", \"from\": 2034, \"to\": 2223, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the vote\", \"from\": 2049, \"to\": 2057}, {\"ngram\": \"a parliament\", \"from\": 2067, \"to\": 2079}, {\"ngram\": \"left-wing, centrist and right-wing blocs\", \"from\": 2094, \"to\": 2134}, {\"ngram\": \"an absolute majority\", \"from\": 2146, \"to\": 2166}, {\"ngram\": \"no agreement\", \"from\": 2168, \"to\": 2180}, {\"ngram\": \"a governing coalition\", \"from\": 2184, \"to\": 2205}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France finds itself in limbo, with a caretaker government, a situation that may now last through the Games.\", \"from\": 2225, \"to\": 2332, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2225, \"end\": 2231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999920754212547, \"rank\": 4.918204155904007e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"limbo\", \"from\": 2248, \"to\": 2253}, {\"ngram\": \"a caretaker government\", \"from\": 2260, \"to\": 2282}, {\"ngram\": \"a situation\", \"from\": 2284, \"to\": 2295}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 2322, \"to\": 2331}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The torch was carried on July 14 past the vacant National Assembly \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 the new parliament has not convened yet \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 by Jean Turco, who at the age of 106 is the oldest former lawmaker in France.\", \"from\": 2334, \"to\": 2526, \"